Hello =F0=9F=91=8B

It=E2=80=99s Pedro http://x.com/peduarte here with another monthly update! =
As always, team picks at the bottom of the email.





RAYCAST =C3=97 TOKYO

We travelled to Tokyo to hang out with our community. Wow. Still trying to=
 find the right words to express how beautiful it was. Japan is our third =
largest user base and for a while they've already been hosting some =
community-driven events. So we decided it was time for us to fly over there=
 and connect with them in real life.

To make the trip worthwhile, we =
hosted two events.

 * Hackathon: We partnered with Anthropic https://www.=
anthropic.com/, Supabase https://supabase.com/, Vercel https://vercel.com/,=
 and AWS Startup Loft https://aws.amazon.com/startups/lp/aws-startup-loft-t=
okyo to host a hackathon with amazing prizes and even better vibes. There =
were over 150 participants, it was crazy. They built Raycast extensions we =
never would've thought of.

 * Meetup: We also hosted a Raycast community =
meetup at the Cybozu https://cybozu.co.jp/ office. Around 60 people showed =
up. It was great. Thomas shared some sneak peeks of Raycast for Windows and=
 some refreshed UI updates. The community did a few lightning talks, and =
Thomas, Steph and I held a fireside panel where people could ask us =
questions.

These events wouldn't have been possible without the help and =
collaboration of lots of people, so here's my heartfelt thanks to all of =
them: Our Japan Ambassadors and community members Yano https://twitter.=
com/@nagauta_jp, Tyki https://twitter.com/@tyykid16, Koyasu https://twitter=
.com/@ux_kys, Seiji https://x.com/se_eiji, Kaita https://twitter.com/@z63d_=
, Yogo https://twitter.com/@yogo_escentier, Adake https://x.com/yuichi_yogo=
, Hirota https://twitter.com/@HiroYuske, Tyler https://x.com/dshukertjr =
from Supabase for being a spectatucular MC and huge contributor to the =
hackathon, Jo https://x.com/jozhukennedy from Anthropic, Nicolas and Shohei=
 https://x.com/jrsyo from Vercel, Kazuhiro https://twitter.com/@0b1tk and =
Sakito https://twitter.com/@sakito from Cybozu for hosting the meetup, AWS =
Startup Loft for hosting the hackathon, our Taiwan Amabassadors Yen =
https://x.com/ridemountainpig and Yiwei https://x.com/1weiho for fying over=
 to just meet us, and finally Stephanie, our Community Manager for =
organising all. Thank you all so much!





KEYBOARD FOR IOS

Our custom keyboard puts dictation, AI commands, snippets, and quicklinks =
at your fingertips. This completely changes the Raycast experience on =
mobile. Building a keyboard was already in our roadmap when we initially =
announced Raycast for iOS, but it was a challenging feature to get right. =
Since launching the keyboard, we've received so much praise from our users!

Check out the video https://youtu.be/lta7_MCTzxo to see it in action!





IN OTHER NEWS

=F0=9F=93=BA Ever wondered how Shopify's CEO, Tobi =
L=C3=BCtke, uses Raycast? Wonder no more. Check out his What's in my =
Raycast https://youtu.be/bRQT_oN51Fw. I had so much fun doing this =
interview.

=F0=9F=94=A5 Read about https://www.raycast.=
com/customers/incidentio how incident.=E2=81=A0io responds to incidents =
faster with Raycast.

=F0=9F=8C=90 OpenAI released ChatGPT Atlas =
https://chatgpt.com/atlas/, their AI browser, and there's already a Raycast=
 Extension for it. Check it out https://www.raycast.=
com/thomas/chatgpt-atlas!

=F0=9F=93=8B Master Clipboard history. Seriously=
, you won't regret it! Watch our video https://youtu.be/dOzTzVtg5lk to =
learn all about it.

=F0=9F=9B=A1=EF=B8=8F We=E2=80=99re enterprise ready =
with our SOC2 Type II certificate. Want to bring it to your company? Let's =
talk =E2=86=92 enterprise@raycast.com

=F0=9F=A7=98=E2=80=8D=E2=99=82=
=EF=B8=8F We're slowing down our release cycle for a little while. See =
Thomas' announcement here https://x.com/thomaspaulmann/status/1976636662705=
705022.

=F0=9F=AA=9F Remember to sign up for the Windows waitlist.





TEAM PICKS

Time for everyone=E2=80=99s favorite part. Team picks!

=F0=9F=91=9C Sandy got this little beauty a couple https://uk.coach.=
com/products/andrea-small-shoulder-bag-in-smooth-leather-with-tonal-hardwar=
e/CT757.html of weeks ago. She said that if Raycast were a handbag, this =
might be it. Never thought of Raycast being a bag before, but here we are!

=F0=9F=97=BA=EF=B8=8F=C2=A0Bruno just found out about Corner https://www.=
corner.inc/ and is enjoying using it to discover new places.

=F0=9F=A7=A5 Jordan picked up this lovely Universal Works fleece jacket =
https://universalworks.com/products/universal-works-uniform-jacket-in-rust-=
wool-fleece. Good choice.

=F0=9F=91=83 Megan's back with her fragrances, =
this time with the Parisian Musc https://matiere-premiere.=
com/products/parisian-musc from Matiere Premiere.

=F0=9F=83=8F Michael =
picked this a few new board games including 7 Wonders Duel =
https://boardgamegeek.com/boardgame/173346/7-wonders-duel.

=F0=9F=92=A3 If you're into collaborative deduction games, Mathieu =
recommends Bomb Busters https://boardgamegeek.com/boardgame/413246/bomb-bus=
ters.

=F0=9F=8E=B4 David recently played Don't Get Got https://bigpotato.=
co.uk/products/dont-get-got and can't recommend it enough.

=F0=9F=8E=B2 Since we're talking about board games, Tirta loves Scoville =
https://boardgamegeek.com/boardgame/145659/scoville!

=F0=9F=87=A9=F0=9F=87=AA Danny wans to call out some his favourite German =
bread: The Sonnenbatzen https://www.schaefers-brot.de/produkte/detail?=
id=3D458.

=F0=9F=91=96 Thomas bought some new trousers from Tokyo, =
including this one https://porterclassic.com/products/moleskin-gene-kelly-p=
ants from Porter Classic.

=F0=9F=91=9F I recently picked up this ALW Slip =
On https://store.moonstar.co.jp/products/detail/201 from Moonstar from =
Tokyo.




That's it for this month. For all changes, check out =
our=C2=A0changelog https://www.raycast.com/changelog.

See you next month!

